videos.description: Matt Linehan connects to Reuben Mwehla for 47 yards into Appalachian State territory.
videos.headline: Linehan hits Mwehla for a big gain

videos.description: Idaho's Armond Hawkins recovers a fumble of Malik Williams to set up the Vandals deep in Appalachian State territory.
videos.headline: Idaho's defense produces turnover

videos.description: Idaho's Kaden Elliss hammers Ike Lewis of Appalachian State for no gain.
videos.headline: Idaho's Elliss hammers Appalachian State receiver

videos.description: Matt Linehan hits Alfonso Onunwor for a 20-yard touchdown to extend Idaho's lead.
videos.headline: Linehan to Onunwor produces  first Idaho TD

videos.description: Matt Linehan finds Joseph Wysocki for a 5-yard touchdown to extend the lead to 17-0 in the 2nd quarter.
videos.headline: Linehan's second TD pass pushes the lead for Idaho

videos.description: Idaho's Sedrick Thomas intercepts Taylor Lamb's pass and 20-yard return sets up Idaho in Appalachian State territory.
videos.headline: Thomas's interception  sets up Idaho in Appalachian State territory

videos.description: Taylor Lamb connects to Ike Lewis for a 38-yard touchdown in the third quarter.
videos.headline: Appalachian State gets its offense uncorked

videos.description: Taylor Lamb to Colin Reed from 6-yards out pulls Appalachian State within one score.
videos.headline: Appalachian State inch closer

videos.description: Taylor Lamb and Ike Lewis connect for a 45-yard touchdown to tie the game in the 4th quarter.
videos.headline: Lamb to Lewis strikes again to tie the game

videos.description: Trey Bender and Jay Taylor tell how Idaho blew a 17-0 lead, and how they need to improve in finishing opponents. Also, the defense of Appalachian State came through with big plays.
videos.headline: Bender and Taylor with the final analysis of Appalachian State's come-from-behind victory
